  "description": "¶Background Information There\u0026rsquo;s a technology company called Librem who is, I think, releasing a smart phone featuring an operating system they\u0026rsquo;ve designed for it, called PureOS. Again, I think - it\u0026rsquo;s tangential to my point, so I haven\u0026rsquo;t looked it up.\nThey made an announcement recently sharing some information about the applications the phone would run, and within the open-source software community, there was immediately criticism. From what I understand, many of the applications are existing free and open-source applications, which have had their appearance altered and are now being sold.\n",
  "name": "Librem should have followed my escalation of communication",
